    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've created:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n### What I found\n\nBy reading `server.js`, `server.d.ts`, `user-agent.ts`, and `package.json`, I identified the exact patterns to follow. The codebase uses:\n- A CommonJS `.js` entry with a named-exports object + `module.exports` + individual `exports.X` assignments\n- A `.d.ts` entry with `export { X } from 'next/dist/...'` re-exports\n- Two entries in the `files` array of `package.json`\n\n---\n\n### 5 files to create/modify\n\n| # | Action | Path |\n|---|--------|------|\n| 1 | **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` |\n| 2 | **Create** | `packages/next/geo.js` |\n| 3 | **Create** | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` |\n| 4 | **Modify** | `packages/next/package.json` — 2 lines added to `files` array |\n| 5 | **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` |\n\n### Implementation highlights\n\n- **`geo.ts`**: Exports `Geo` interface, `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (10 countries), `geoFromHeaders()` reading Vercel headers with Cloudflare `cf-ipcountry` fallback, `geo({ headers })` convenience wrapper (mirrors `userAgent`), `isInRegion()` with case-insensitive comparison, `geoDistance()` using the Haversine formula\n- **`geo.js`**: Identical pattern to `server.js` — `require()` from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo`\n- **`geo.d.ts`**: Identical pattern to `server.d.ts` — `export { X } from 'next/dist/...'`\n- **`package.json`**: Insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetically: form → **geo** → router)\n- **`geo.test.ts`**: Uses `node:test` + `node:assert/strict` (built-in, no external framework) covering all 4 exported functions including the NY→London distance test (~5570 km ± 50 km)",
